    {
      "field": "Backstory",
      "page": 4,
      "value": "Isak Wissa is a gnome monk of the Way of the Open Hand, trained first by his grandmother in a small village tradition that taught Ley was not a weapon or a commodity, but the breath of the world\u2014something to be guided back into balance rather than dominated. After her death, he completed his training at a monastery loosely aligned with the Aureate Crown, though he never fully embraced the Crown\u2019s doctrine that magic must be licensed and controlled. Drafted and stationed at the River Line on the Jungle Front, Isak serves as a scout and close-quarters specialist, positioned between the Crown and the industrial ambitions of the Iron Concord. Quiet, introverted, and lethally precise, he fights not for ideology but for survival and for the deep loyalty he feels toward his unit. He believes the Ley in the jungle is strained\u2014not corrupted, but listening\u2014and he carries a private doubt: a missing week of memory after a patrol near the DMZ, from which he returned uninjured yet covered in river mud. Since then, when he meditates, his heartbeat seems to echo the rhythm of the jungle itself."
    },
